<%- include('../../partials/head') %>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-50">

  <main class="container mx-auto mt-10 px-6 sm:px-8">
    <section class="bg-white shadow-xl rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-12 space-y-12">

      <!-- Title -->
      <div class="text-center space-y-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-red-600">Cancellation Options</h1>
        <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Plans change, and we understand. Our cancellation policies are designed to give both 
          <span class="font-semibold">guests and hosts</span> flexibility and peace of mind.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Guest Cancellations -->
      <div class="space-y-4 border-t pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 flex items-center gap-2">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-user text-red-500"></i> Guest Cancellations
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Guests can cancel their bookings according to the cancellation policy chosen by the host. 
          Depending on the timing, refunds may vary:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Flexible:</strong> Full refund if canceled up to 24 hours before check-in.</li>
          <li><strong>Moderate:</strong> Full refund if canceled 5 days before check-in.</li>
          <li><strong>Strict:</strong> 50% refund if canceled at least 7 days before check-in.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Host Cancellations -->
      <div class="space-y-4 border-t pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 flex items-center gap-2">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-house text-red-500"></i> Host Cancellations
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We strongly discourage host cancellations. However, in cases where a host must cancel:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
          <li>Guests receive a full refund automatically.</li>
          <li>Hosts may face penalties or account restrictions for repeated cancellations.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Exceptional Circumstances -->
      <div class="space-y-4 border-t pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 flex items-center gap-2">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-exclamation-circle text-red-500"></i> Exceptional Circumstances
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          In rare cases such as natural disasters, medical emergencies, or government travel 
          restrictions, guests and hosts may cancel without penalties under our 
          <span class="font-semibold">Extenuating Circumstances Policy</span>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQs -->
      <div class="space-y-4 border-t pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 flex items-center gap-2">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-question text-red-500"></i> Frequently Asked Questions
        </h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
          <li><strong>How do I cancel a booking?</strong> — Go to "My Trips" and select "Cancel Reservation".</li>
          <li><strong>When will I get my refund?</strong> — Refunds are processed within 5–10 business days.</li>
          <li><strong>Can I change my dates instead of canceling?</strong> — Yes, you can request a date change with the host.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-8 rounded-2xl text-center space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-600">Need help with cancellations?</h3>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/help" 
             class="bg-gray-700 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl shadow hover:bg-gray-900 transition">
            Visit Help Center
          </a>
          <a href="/" 
             class="bg-red-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl shadow hover:bg-red-700 transition">
            ← Back to Home
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </section>
  </main>

</body>
</html>
